{"word":"H5162 - נָחַם - nâcham - naw-kham' - Comfort","slug":"H5162","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָחַם</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâcham"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-kham'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Comfort"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05D7;&#x05DD; - na&#x0302;cham</b> - <i>naw-kham'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>sigh</i>, that is, <i>breathe</i> strongly; by implication to <i>be sorry</i>, that is, (in a favorable sense) to <i>pity</i>, <i>console</i> or (reflexively) <i>rue</i>; or (unfavorably) to <i>avenge</i> (oneself): - comfort (self), ease [one&rsquo;s self], repent (-er, -ing, self)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4505\">H4505</a>, <a href=\"#/H5149\">H5149</a>, <a href=\"#/H5150\">H5150</a>, <a href=\"#/H5151\">H5151</a>, <a href=\"#/H5163\">H5163</a>, <a href=\"#/H5164\">H5164</a>, <a href=\"#/H5165\">H5165</a>, <a href=\"#/H5166\">H5166</a>, <a href=\"#/H5167\">H5167</a>, <a href=\"#/H8575\">H8575</a>, <a href=\"#/H8576\">H8576</a>"}]}